Setting vs Baking✨
Can you spot the difference? 

Setting: This technique involves using a light layer of a powder as close to your skintone to reduce shine and make your makeup last longer. This is suitable for all skin types 

Baking: This technique involves placing a translucent setting powder, letting it sit for a minute or two and then dusting the excess away. This gives a high coverage, lasts all day and is perfect for oily skin
